Class TabularUploadError

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.util.csv.TabularUploadError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.context.MessageSourceResolvable

    public final class TabularUploadError
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.springframework.context.MessageSourceResolvable

    Similar to Spring's FieldError class, but specifically represents an error in a tabular file upload.

    Immutable.

      • forField

        public static TabularUploadError forField(int rowNumber,
                          java.lang.String columnName,
                          java.lang.Class<?> fieldType,
                          java.lang.String code,
                          java.lang.Object[] arguments,
                          java.lang.String defaultMessage)

        Creates an error for a particular cell.

        Row numbers are 1-based to correspond to Excel.

        Parameters:
        rowNumber - the associated row's number (1-based)
        columnName - the associated column's name. Must not be null.
        fieldType - the expected type of the target field
        code - the primary error code
        arguments - any necessary message arguments. May be null.
        defaultMessage - the default message to use if no codes could be resolved
        Returns:
        a new instance
